cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on image-to-image translation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel unified model that involves disentangling input images into latent representations and encouraging the generator to learn multi-mappings, which requires a combination of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper uses adversarial training, which is a common technique in generative models (cs.GR) and specifically in image-to-image translation. Finally, the paper evaluates its method through experiments, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
